                        <interp inst="t18500916-name-186" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LEONARD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City-policeman,</hi> 621). I took the prisoner, and found on him one shilling—I received this purse from Mrs. Mayers—there is a half-sovereign, and a sixpence in it—she took the half-crown out to reward the young man that followed the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MRS. MAYERS</hi>. This is my purse, and the one I lost—I received it from Nevan—it has the half-sovereign in it, and the sixpence with two holes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was coming home and was taken; I did not see the purse.</p>
